how to leave my job gracefully i am currently working as an intern i started in feb and was supposed to go thru dec well at my month evaluation they told me my last day would be august th my manager implied that my position was going to be cut due to financial reasons but weeks later i find out that she plans on attending a job fair in the fall to find my replacement she doesn't know that i know this ever since my evaluation she does nothing but praise me and my work leaving me incredibly frustrated as to why they are getting rid of me as my last day is approaching she wants the whole department to go to lunch to wish me well everyone in the office seems surprised when i tell them i'm leaving and they assume that i'm leaving on my own will how do i explain to them when they ask how the job search has been going that i had to take a temporary dept store job because i couldn't find another job in my field and it wasn't my choice to leave should i just keep quiet you should definitely keep quite although that sucks it's unfortunate that this is happening to you but the only thing that you can do is look for another job also don't forget to ask your manager and anyone else that you worked closely with for a letter of recommendation best of luck Criticism of government response to Hurricane Katrina Piccolo Junior Saga Ben Johnson (athlete) Wal-Mart Unemployment Pitaten Leeds United F.C. John R. Bolton Shaggy dog story Plame affair Avenue Q EastEnders Social rule Kodocha StarCraft: Uprising Eutheism, dystheism, and maltheism The Star Wars Holiday Special 2005 trial of Michael Jackson Condon Committee Roswell UFO incident The Contender (television series) Friends The Subtle Knife Good Times I Want to Hold Your Hand Normal distribution Ocean's Twelve Microeconomics Extreme Programming Intelligent design Theodicy Jack Charlton Kingdom Hearts: Chain of Memories Theory of conduct 2000 Australian Grand Prix Incarnations of Immortality Dilbert 1957 World Series Continuation War 